Canada-based mining company Semafo on Monday announced that two employees of a local contractor at its Mana mine, in Burkina Faso, have been killed. The accident occurred when the driver of a light vehicle in which the employees were travelling lost control on a haul road to the mine. No other vehicles were involved in the accident. Semafo said the contractor was investigating the cause of the accident. Semafo operates the Boungou and Mana mines in Burkina Faso.